# Rules map (index-first routing)

**Do not load every file in this directory into context.**  
Always-on entries are `../AGENTS.md` (universal, all harnesses) and `../instructions/agent-instructions.md` (kilo). Both **point** at rules. Load a rule body only when its trigger fires or you must enforce a gate.

## Always-Active (pointers in AGENTS.md / instructions)

These rules are referenced from the always-loaded instruction files. Load the rule body when you encounter the trigger condition.

| Rule | Trigger | Size |
|---|---|---|
| `code-quality.md` | Writing or modifying ANY code | medium |
| `skill-compliance.md` | After loading any skill (binding commitment) | medium |
| `self-grounded-verification.md` | Verification, self-review, "done" claims | medium |
| `autonomy-safety.md` | Auto-approved tools, AFK, waived per-step prompts | medium |
| `git-safety.md` | Git staging, committing, pushing; pre-commit memory checkpoint | small |

## On-Demand (load when trigger fires)

| Rule | Trigger | Size |
|---|---|---|
| `tdd.md` | Logic modules / algorithms / services | medium |
| `grooming.md` | Plans, ambiguous requirements, complex tasks | small |
| `ubiquitous-language.md` | Logic that introduces or renames domain terms | small |
| `slicing.md` | Feature plans / `task.md` checklists | small |
| `skills-discovery.md` | Need to choose a skill (index-first) | small |
| `command-routing.md` | User request maps to a slash/command workflow | tiny |
| `memory.md` | Capture / recall / consolidate / evict memory | small |
| `requirements-driven-dev.md` | Adapter → load `requirements-driven-dev` skill | tiny |

## Layering

```
AGENTS.md / instructions (always) → rule pointer → rule body (on fire)
                                  → skills/INDEX → SKILL.md → references/*
```

## Anti-patterns

- Bulk-reading `rules/*.md` at session start — load only when triggered
- Modifying `.agents/`, skills, or rules without loading `skill-author` and checking https://agentskills.io + https://agents.md
- Duplicating rule text into every skill (link instead)
- Project forks of global rules without a documented overlay reason
- Loading skills without checking `skills/INDEX.md` first

